# ------------------------------------------------------------------
SU(N) pure-gauge density-of-states computations including evolution
Can use either over-relaxed quasi-heatbath or hybrid Monte Carlo for updates

For N=3 pg_ora reproduces milc_qcd/pure_gauge/test/su3_ora.2 (blame for test su3_ora.1 mentions "new random number generator" from commit c05e59d)

However, pg_ora and pg_llr_ora seem strangely sensitive to roundoff accumulation --- see github.com/milc-qcd/milc_qcd/issues/44

When adapting the SU(3) LLR input below for different SU(N) gauge groups, the energy is proportional to beta times the plaquette (normalized out of N)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------



# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sample input file for ora:
prompt 0
nx 4
ny 4
nz 4
nt 4
iseed 41

warms 0
trajecs 3
traj_between_meas 3

beta 6.0
ora_steps 4
qhb_steps 4

reload_serial config.SU3.4444
forget
# ------------------------------------------------------------------



# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sample input file for hmc:
prompt 0
nx 4
ny 4
nz 4
nt 4
iseed 41

warms 0
trajecs 3
traj_between_meas 3

beta 6.0
hmc_steps 15
traj_length 1.0

reload_serial config.SU3.4444
forget
# ------------------------------------------------------------------



# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sample input file for llr:
prompt 0
nx 4
ny 4
nz 4
nt 4
iseed 41

warms 3
trajecs 3
traj_between_meas 10

beta 6.0
hmc_steps 15
traj_length 1.0

Emin -60.0
delta 6.0
a = 1.0
ait 10

reload_serial config.SU3.4444
forget
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
